    slug: "glorious-sermons-from-the-haram",
    description: `Glorious Sermons from the Haram is an English-language compilation of selected Friday sermons (khutbah) delivered at Masjid al-Haram, the Grand Mosque in Makkah, which surrounds the Ka'bah — the holiest site in Islam. The sermons in this collection were originally delivered in Arabic by the imams and khateebs appointed by the Saudi Arabian government to lead the prayers and deliver the weekly Friday sermons at the most visited mosque on earth, where millions of Muslims from every corner of the globe gather throughout the year for worship. The book presents English translations of these powerful sermons, making their guidance, wisdom, and spiritual exhortation accessible to readers who do not understand Arabic and who wish to benefit from the knowledge and advice dispensed from Islam's most sacred pulpit.

The sermons in this collection cover a wide range of topics that are central to the faith and practice of Islam. They address the fundamentals of Islamic belief, including the oneness of Allah, the role of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) as the final messenger, the reality of the Hereafter, and the importance of sincerity in worship. They also deal with practical aspects of Muslim life, including the importance of maintaining family ties, the rights of parents over their children, the obligation of honesty in business dealings, the prohibition of usury (riba) and corruption, the importance of unity among Muslims, the duty of enjoining good and forbidding evil, and the need for patience and trust in Allah during times of hardship and trial. The sermons delivered during the months of Ramadan and Dhul Hijjah carry special significance, as they address the spiritual opportunities presented by fasting, prayer, charity, and pilgrimage.

The translation maintains the rhetorical power and emotional resonance of the original Arabic sermons, which are known for their eloquent language, their grounding in Quranic verses and authentic hadith, and their ability to move the hearts of listeners even across language barriers. The translators have worked to preserve the structure and flow of the sermons while ensuring that the English rendering is natural and idiomatic. Each sermon begins with praise and glorification of Allah and invocation of blessings upon the Prophet, following the established format for Islamic sermons, before proceeding to the main topic. The book includes contextual notes that help readers understand specific references, historical events, and Arabic idioms that may be unfamiliar to English-speaking audiences. This collection is valuable for anyone who wants to experience the power and depth of the sermons delivered at the Grand Mosque, for imams and khateebs who are looking for models of effective sermon composition and delivery, for teachers who want to use the sermons as educational material, and for general readers who seek spiritual upliftment and practical guidance from one of Islam's most important platforms for public religious instruction.`,
    metaDescription: "Glorious Sermons from the Haram is an English translation of Friday sermons from Masjid al-Haram in Makkah. Covers faith, family, and social guidance."
